<p id="Par13" class="p">We can specify a probability model for dependent multivariate observations, by expressing the 
 <italic class="italic">d</italic> dimensional joint cumulative distribution 
 <italic class="italic">F</italic> in terms of its marginals 
 <italic class="italic">F</italic>
 <sub class="sub">1</sub>,
 <italic class="italic">…F</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">d</italic>
 </sub>, and the associated copula 
 <bold class="bold">
  <italic class="italic">C</italic>
 </bold>, following Sklar’s theorem
 <sup class="sup">
  <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR57" class="xref">57</xref>,
  <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR58" class="xref">58</xref>
 </sup>.
